                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 6.406,
                                "byte_start": 108544,
                                "byte_stop": 134248,
                                "text": "In case Number 11-246, Match-E-Be-Nash-She-Wish Band of Potawatomi Indians v. Patchak."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 6.406,
                                "stop": 9.588,
                                "byte_start": 134248,
                                "byte_stop": 146996,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has the opinion of the Court."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.588,
                        "stop": 276.088,
                        "byte_start": 146996,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.588,
                                "stop": 18.76,
                                "byte_start": 146996,
                                "byte_stop": 183672,
                                "text": "This is a case about sovereign immunity and prudential standing, maybe not what you\u0027ve all come for today.[Laughter]"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.76,
                                "stop": 25.006,
                                "byte_start": 183672,
                                "byte_stop": 208645,
                                "text": "The question is whether to allow a suit brought by respondent, David Patchak to proceed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.006,
                                "stop": 29.448,
                                "byte_start": 208645,
                                "byte_stop": 226408,
                                "text": "Respondent Patchak owns property in rural Michigan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.448,
                                "stop": 42.486,
                                "byte_start": 226408,
                                "byte_stop": 278549,
                                "text": "He brought suit when the Department of Interior acquired property for an Indian tribe, the Match-E-Be-Nash-She-Wish Band of Potawatomi Indians to enable them to build a casino."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.486,
                                "stop": 57.876,
                                "byte_start": 278549,
                                "byte_stop": 340093,
                                "text": "Patchak thinks a casino will change the character of the area and cause him economic, environmental, and aesthetic harm and he says the Government lacked the authority, the legal authority, to acquire this land under the Indian Reorganization Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 57.876,
                                "stop": 64.655,
                                "byte_start": 340093,
                                "byte_stop": 367261,
                                "text": "So, he asked the Court to reverse the Government\u0027s acquisition of the land by divesting it of title."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.655,
                                "stop": 77.243,
                                "byte_start": 367261,
                                "byte_stop": 417520,
                                "text": "When citizens like Patchak contest the legality of agency action and seek non-monetary relief, they bring a suit under a statute called the Administrative Procedure Act or APA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.243,
                                "stop": 87.498,
                                "byte_start": 417520,
                                "byte_stop": 458585,
                                "text": "That Act contains a provision waiving the Government\u0027s sovereign immunity which is the legal doctrine that historically prevents governments from being sued."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.498,
                                "stop": 97.665,
                                "byte_start": 458585,
                                "byte_stop": 499231,
                                "text": "But the APA\u0027s waiver of immunity has an exception, when another statute forbids the suit, the APA\u0027s waiver of immunity does not control."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.665,
                                "stop": 116.472,
                                "byte_start": 499231,
                                "byte_stop": 574464,
                                "text": "The tribe and the Government contends that in this circumstance another statute called Quiet Title Act does forbid the suit because they say, that\u0027s statute retains the Government\u0027s immunity from any suits challenging the Government\u0027s title to Indian trust lands."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.472,
                                "stop": 120.048,
                                "byte_start": 574464,
                                "byte_stop": 588779,
                                "text": "That\u0027s the first question we address in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.048,
                                "stop": 128.833,
                                "byte_start": 588779,
                                "byte_stop": 623888,
                                "text": "We reject the Government\u0027s argument because we think the Quiet Title Act addresses a different kind of suit than the one Patchak brought."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.833,
                                "stop": 136.545,
                                "byte_start": 623888,
                                "byte_stop": 654817,
                                "text": "The Quiet Title Act is about, this is going to surprise you, but the Quiet Title Act is about quiet title actions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.545,
                                "stop": 145.545,
                                "byte_start": 654817,
                                "byte_stop": 690761,
                                "text": "And a quiet title action is a very particular kind of suit which requires the person suing himself to claim ownership of the land in question."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.545,
                                "stop": 156.64,
                                "byte_start": 690761,
                                "byte_stop": 735169,
                                "text": "If Patchak claims to own the land here, the Quiet Title Act would control and it would indeed bar the suit because it prevents quiet title actions involving Indian Lands."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.64,
                                "stop": 165.997,
                                "byte_start": 735169,
                                "byte_stop": 772577,
                                "text": "But because Patchak does not claim ownership of the land, he is not bringing a quiet title action and the Quiet Title Act simply has no application."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.997,
                                "stop": 171.7,
                                "byte_start": 772577,
                                "byte_stop": 795355,
                                "text": "Instead, the APA\u0027s general waiver of sovereign immunity controls."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.7,
                                "stop": 180.408,
                                "byte_start": 795355,
                                "byte_stop": 830255,
                                "text": "But tribe and Government also have another objection to Patchak\u0027s suit that he does not have what we\u0027ve called prudential standing to bring it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.408,
                                "stop": 187.98,
                                "byte_start": 830255,
                                "byte_stop": 860557,
                                "text": "Recall that Patchak says the Government lacked authority to acquire this property under the Indian Reorganization Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.98,
                                "stop": 198.897,
                                "byte_start": 860557,
                                "byte_stop": 904234,
                                "text": "The prudential standing argument is that Patchak does not fall within what we\u0027ve called the zone-of-interests regulated by that statute and so cannot bring this lawsuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.897,
                                "stop": 207.869,
                                "byte_start": 904234,
                                "byte_stop": 940074,
                                "text": "That argument depends on the idea that the Indian Reorganization Act is not about land use, but only about land acquisition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.869,
                                "stop": 216.715,
                                "byte_start": 940074,
                                "byte_stop": 975496,
                                "text": "If that were true, Patchak couldn\u0027t bring his suit because it\u0027s only an objection to the way the Band is going -- the tribe is going to use the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 216.715,
                                "stop": 228.972,
                                "byte_start": 975496,
                                "byte_stop": 1024502,
                                "text": "So, the suit would not be sufficiently connected to the statute that Patchak says was violated, but here, that\u0027s just not true and so we reject the prudential standing argument, too."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.972,
                                "stop": 233.967,
                                "byte_start": 1024502,
                                "byte_stop": 1044459,
                                "text": "The Indian Reorganization Act serves to promote Indian economic development."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.967,
                                "stop": 250.325,
                                "byte_start": 1044459,
                                "byte_stop": 1109870,
                                "text": "So, when the Department decides whether to acquire land for a band or a tribe it thinks a good deal about what the tribe would do with that land, including what potential conflicts the use will create and indeed it did so in this very case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 250.325,
                                "stop": 262.291,
                                "byte_start": 1109870,
                                "byte_stop": 1157726,
                                "text": "The upshot is that because the Indian Reorganization Act is about land use, a neighbor who objects to that use has prudential standing to bring an action under the APA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 262.291,
                                "stop": 272.382,
                                "byte_start": 1157726,
                                "byte_stop": 1198164,
                                "text": "We accordingly hold that Patchak suit may proceed and because that was the conclusion reached by the D.C. Circuit Court of Appeals, we affirm its judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 272.382,
                                "stop": 276.088,
                                "byte_start": 1198164,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
